description:
Job Responsibilities:
- Perform database administration and support services in Linux, Windows, IBM z/OS and Cloud platform;
- Implement and support infrastructure solutions in sophisticated, high-performance trading environments that demand stability, high throughput and low latency;
- Provide support and implementation work to application teams including database setup and SQL performance analysis;
- Provide advice for operating policies, technical architecture and configuration of database system;
- Administer and manage Oracle / DB2 Databases including monitoring, troubleshooting, installation, patching and upgrade, performance tuning, backup and recovery, stress test, capacity planning;
- Implement compliance standards and perform regular system compliance review and proactively assesses exposure area;
- Maintain high system availability and ensure all database systems work properly;
- Review SQL, stored procedures and application interfaces with databases;
- Manage vendor to ensure the highest quality delivery and implementation

Job Requirement:
- With at least 7 years of working experience in managing and supporting Oracle / DB2 databases;
- Solid experience with SQL, PL/SQL and shell script/programming would be an advantage;
- Advanced knowledge of Oracle database including RAC, ASM, DataGuard, data partitioning, load balancing, JDBC, ODBC and integration with J2EE applications;
- Strong in SQL and stored procedures;
- Advanced knowledge of database security, backup and recovery, and performance monitoring standards;
- Strong hands-on experience in developing script solutions for process improvement and automation; 
- Experiences in AWS RDS, MS SQL, MongoDB, DB2 PureScale and HADR is an advantage;
- Understanding of relational and dimensional data modelling;
- Experience in system programming and administration on Linux or Windows Platform;
- Project management experience in sizable scale technology infrastructure implementation;
- Proactive, strong troubleshooting, diagnostic and analytical skills;
- Degree holder in Computer science, Computer engineering, information technology or relevant discipline

Applicants who do not hear from us within 6 weeks may consider their applications unsuccessful. Personal data provided will only be used for the purpose of employment application to HKEX.

Responsibilities:

Building Continuous Integration (CI) and Continuous Delivery (CD) pipelines;
Driving high levels of automation into those pipelines;
Mentoring and coaching other teams on how to continue to maintain and adjust their pipelines;
Automating the configuration and delivery of infrastructure and software releases, and production deployment of new software releases;
Design and develop tools and automation to minimize delivery time and increase developer productivity;
Working with teams to create runbooks and other operational support documentation to improve operationalization of product releases;
Investigating and implementing new software platforms that support service lifecycle operations. E.g. monitoring / telemetry, release management, secret management, automated testing, etc;
Automation of operation functions in Python, Shell, and various platform- specific environments.

Requirements:

Degree holder in Computer Science, Information Technology or related disciplines;
Certificate holder in ITIL / AWS Certified Solutions Architect or equivalent
5 years' working experience in software delivery and system administration, experience as a database developer or DBA would be advantageous;
Significant experience in automating software delivery on public clouds would be advantageous;
Good knowledge in Git, GitLab, Jenkins, Babnoo, Nexus, Selenium, Ansible, Capistrano, Consul, Terraform, Pack, SOAP-UI, Junit, JIRA, Rally, Docker, Kubernetes, Envoy, Istio, Cucumber, DataDog, Honeycomb, ets;
Can work independently under limited supervision;
Good communication skills.
We offer competitive salary package and career development opportunity. Free company coach is provided.  Interested parties, please quote our reference number and apply with full resume, present and expected salary, by clicking “APPLY NOW”. 

We are an equal opportunity employer and welcome applications from all qualified candidates. Information provided will be treated in strict confidence and only be used for consideration of your application for the relevant post within HGC Global Communications Limited. Personal data provided by job applicants will be used strictly according to our Personal Information Collection Statement, a copy of which will be available upon written request. Information of unsuccessful candidates will be destroyed within six months.

Responsibilities:

* Analyse data from property management system;

* Generate and disseminate reports;

* Implement data flow;



Requirements:

* University degree or above, major in IT or statistics related discipline;

* 1-4 years working experience in handling data;

* Good knowledge in Python;

* Knowledge on Software development Life Cycle, MSSQL (SSMS, SSIS), ETL, data cleansing;

* Knowledge in Tableau is an advantage;

* With strong sense of responsibility, self-motivated, committed, strong analytical and problem solving skills, good interpersonal & communication skills, team player;

* Detail oriented and well organized;

DEAR TALENT, YOUR MOVE!

Being the new rising airline since 2013, we are the Hong Kong’s only Low Cost Carrier (LCC) offering you safe and flexible service options to Hong Kong and beyond.

We’re on a mission to inspire you to be different, to shake things up, to inspire the spirit of adventure by bringing you to fascinating destinations that few others serve.

Spread your wings and fly with us!


What will you do? 

Perform exploratory data analysis and develop business values from data;
Build and deploy the predictive model on cloud;
Understand the data and create insightful visualization to facilitate user understanding;
Examine data schema and ensure/maintain data quality;
Identify opportunities for leveraging corporate data and drive data-driven solutions to meet business goals;
Explore innovative ways for data integration to enforce good governance on data management and regulatory compliance;
Assess the potential usefulness and validity of data sources;
Act as a Data Steward of the organization, conduct a Privacy Impact Assessment, govern the internal data usage and monitor the third party regularly to ensure the handling of personal data (not limited to access, transfer and retention of data) is in line with the data handling manuals and guidelines;
Support ad-hoc duties as assigned.

We are a perfect match, if you are:

Bachelor’s degree, preferably in Mathematics, Statistics, Computer Science related discipline;
Minimum 2 years of experience relating to Data Analytics and Data integration;
Knowledge in SQL, Python is required;
Experience in statistical libraries by using python;
Experience in the solution of ETL, cleaning, desensitization;
Experience in data visualization tools, such as Data Studio, PowerBI;
Experience in Linux is preferred;
Knowledge and  hands-on experience on GCP platform and tools including BigQuery, Data Fusion, Compute Engine, Cloud Function, Pub/Sup, Source Repositories;
Good communication and presentation skills;
Airline or travel industry knowledge is highly beneficial.

Your Future Work Life?

Work flexibly with staggered working hours and flexible workplace
Dress Casual and Smart everyday
Work in a newly-designed office with open seating, stylish breakout areas, game room, gym and free coffee…
Work with a group of energetic and multicultural professionals (up to 50 nationalities!)
Have great fun in Snack Friday, New Year Market, Fly with your Kids Day, Basketball Team…
Have your voice heard through Townhalls, Crew forums, CEO live sessions etc.

What will you enjoy?

Fly anywhere we fly for free plus taxes during leisure with your friends and family
Special privileges to buy duty free products
Career Express



You will be inspired by our core values.
You will be inspired by our vibrant, efficient and entrepreneurial spirit. Join our fun, collaborative and reliable team to ignite your dream!



Interested? It’s time to have YOUR MOVE!
If you're ready to embark your adventure, start by clicking the ‘Apply now’ and get on the plane to fly with HK Express!

Responsibilities
*Responsible for internal system development, implementation, maintenance, documentation and training;
*User requirements gathering and work closely with internal users

Requirements
*Bachelor Degree in Computer Science or equivalent;
*2 years or above relevant experience;
*Hands on C# / VB .NET /.Net Core, APIs, Web Apps, SQL Server / MySQL;
*Experience in HTML5, CSS, JQUERY, JAVASCRIPT, REACT is an advantage;
*A self-motivated team player with good interpersonal and communication skills;
*Able to work independently to meet project deadlines;
*Immediately available will be an advantage;

AUGMENTED CREATIVITY LAB

Senior AI System Engineer / AI System Engineer (in the rank of Research Fellow / Senior Research Assistant / Research Assistant) (PR0444/21-22)

The Augmented Creativity Lab at Hong Kong Baptist University invites applications for the Senior AI System Engineer/AI System Engineer position. The selected candidates will work with a group of renowned interdisciplinary researchers, focusing on an AI-based Art Tech project addressing human-machine co-creativity research. More information about the project could be found at https://research.hkbu.edu.hk/highlighted-projects/building-platform-technologies-for-symbiotic-creativity-in-hong-kong.

The appointees are expected to perform the following roles:
Design the architecture of demo/system/platform of symbiotic performance incorporating with AI research engineer, AI scientist and artist; and
Develop the demo/system/platform of symbiotic performance.
Potential candidates should have/be:

A master’s degree in Computer Science, Electronic Engineering, Information Engineering, Mathematics or relevant disciplines with substantial years of related experience.
Candidates with less experience but with strong R&D record may also be considered;
Solid system development experience in one or more of the following domains: NLP, computer vision, streaming multimedia, animation generation, etc;
Experience in Unity based animation generation; Hardware (like optical camera, depth camera, motion sensor or wearable devices devices) based programming experience is preferred;
Solid hands-on coding skills on Python/C/C++/Java;
Full-stack coding experience in mainstreaming front end and back end framework;
Familiar with deep learning frameworks of PyTorch / TensorFlow; GPU programming of CUDA is required and Mindspore is a plus;
Preferably be a plus if familiar with multimedia programming of streaming encoding and decoding;
Preferably familiar with the application of Deep Learning/algorithms, especially with foundation model, transformer model, GANs, GNNs, RL, etc.; 
Strong self-motivation and be able to work independently;
Strong communication skills, the ability to communicate effectively and manage relationships with stakeholders coming from both technical and non-technical backgrounds; and
Fluent in English with good written and oral communication skills.
Initial appointment will be offered on a fixed-term contract of two years. Re-appointment thereafter will be subject to mutual agreement and availability of funding.

Rank and salary will be commensurate with qualifications and experience.

Application Procedure:

Applications are invited to submit their applications at the HKBU e-Recruitment System (jobs.hkbu.edu.hk). Those not invited for interview 4 months after submission of application may consider their applications unsuccessful. Details of the University’s Personal Information Collection Statement can be found at http://hro.hkbu.edu.hk/pics.

The University reserves the right not to make an appointment for the posts advertised, and the appointment will be made according to terms and conditions then applicable at the time of offer.

Review of applications will be ongoing until the positions are filled.

AUGMENTED CREATIVITY LAB

Senior AI Research Engineer / AI Research Engineer (in the rank of Research Fellow / Senior Research Assistant / Research Assistant) (PR0443/21-22)

